Text.string: The Destroyer's gonna be released! We're all gonna die! I knew I should've joined the Children of the Vault! Yaghaghghgh!
Holy crap.
Whoo! A Catch-A-Ride on the legendary planet of Nekrotafeyo! How about that? Now you can ride to Mr. DeLeon in style!
Hey, Vault Hunter! I'm Sparrow. Typhon asked me to show you around!
Sparrow, what the hell? Typhon says the universe is in danger! We don't have time for a tour.
Go to hell, Grouse! Tour time!
FYI, I did all the interior decorating! Nice, right? Just because you're marooned on a deadly planet doesn't mean you can't make it feel like home!
That's Typhon's Vercuvian ham supply! He keeps one on him at all times!
Sparrow, open your eyes. The Vault Hunter doesn't like you, and you're irrelevant to their mission.
Whatever! You're irrelevant to... my ass!
On the house, Vault Hunter. You're gonna need it!

In addition to the end of the world, now the Eridian slab in my lab, or my “lab slab”, has seemingly reactivated itself. Go investigate, Vault Hunter. The Eridians would have left nothing to chance. Perhaps they left us a final message!
So THIS is the Eridian homeworld. After all this time...
I suspect this has something to do with the analyzer you picked up from the Vault. See what happens if you use it.
Interesting.
Strangely familiar.
Strange.
All right!
Crimson Raiders to the bridge.
Okay, this might get weird, you guys. Hold on tight.
Nekrotafeyo...
Nekrotafeyo...
Nekrotafeyo...
Nekrotafeyo...

Well, you did right by Maya and killed that bastard Troy, but this ain't the end of the adventure, amigo. I know I haven't always spoken kindly of Pandora, but it's still my home. And we gotta save it.
The pleasure is all yours.
Certainly know how to make one feel warm and welcome, don't you?
Must you be so dour? Honestly.
I'd tell you to cheer up, but honestly, it seems like this might be the most cheerful ya get.
You know it.
Oh yeah.
I do, yes.
You called it, boyo.
Well, put 'em in, Vault Hunter!
No sense waiting around. Get down there, Vault Hunter. Find Typhon DeLeon.
Vault Hunter, we're tracking Typhon DeLeon's ECHO frequency and sending the coordinates to you.

This is all quite overwhelming. First Pandora was a Vault the entire time, now we've located the Eridian homeworld, and you're about to meet Typhon DeLeon in the flesh. If you'll excuse me, I must take a power nap in my saurian.
Yo, Lilith. Maliwan's here. And by the looks of it, super dead.
Lilith. Maliwan's here. Dead Maliwan, that is.
Maliwan is on the planet, Lilith. Their corpses rot.
Maliwan's in the neighborhood, Lilith. Dead—wasn't me. Yet.
How could Maliwan have known about Nekrotafeyo? Stay sharp, killer.
[yawning] And I wake, viscous and refreshed! You know, Typhon DeLeon was the reason I became an Eridian researcher. If anyone knows how to save the universe, it's him.
Somehow, the Calypsos knew about the Destroyer being imprisoned inside Pandora. That was their goal all along. Should Tyreen leech the Destroyer... well, you are what you eat.
Vault Hunter, over here! I am ecstatic to see you. Typhon DeLeon is waiting for you. Please, enter.
I am Grouse, primary steward to Typhon DeLeon. Because my counterpart is inferior in every way, DeLeon has charged ME with greeting you. So... greetings.
Master hates you, Sparrow. He'd scrap you in a heartbeat. Next time his toilet breaks... you're a goner.
Toilets perform a vital function! I'd be honored.
What took ya so long, Vault Hunter? We got a universe to save!
What? You were expecting someone less handsome?
Glad you made it! Bet it was a schlep! Here's a little somethin' for makin' the trip!
I want that gun.
I really want that gun.
That gun must be mine.
Gun. Gun gun. Gun gun gun! Gun.
Well, it runs on Eridium, so if you got some, I'm always happy to make ya a gun or two. But right now I gotta show you somethin'. This way!
Hey, bots. I'm taking the Vault Hunter to the Machine. Don't let anyone inside, Maliwan or otherwise!
Now's our chance to prove our worth!
Won't matter. It's the end of the universe.
Eh-heh-heh-heh—we'll see about that.
This laser whip's been handy. Helps me keep up in my sundown years. Plus, whips are great! Lasers, too.

By now you've figured out Pandora's a planet-sized Vault. Eridians called it “the Great Vault” or something. A long time ago, they crammed an inter-dimensional monstrosity in there called the Destroyer. Wasn't easy, but they did it.
If that happens, well... they named it the Destroyer for a reason.

The Eridians sacrificed their whole civilization to lock that thing away. They were smart, those aliens. The Eridians had a back up plan, just in case someone was meshugga enough to release the Destroyer.

Behind this door is an ancient Eridian astrokinetic Vault-powered phase engine, something or other. I just call it “the machine”. Pretty nifty. And the colors! Those Eridians knew how to make an entrance, right?
This was the machine that locked away the Destroyer the first time. And it can do it again, too! But we need four Vault Keys to get in. You already got three of 'em, right?
Promethea. I found the first Vault there, ya know.
Eden-6. It ain't no paradise.
Pandora! My home.
There's one last Key and I know where it is! Head's up, though—it's kind of a schlep! And it won't be easy! Eh, but I'm sure you're up for it. You're a Vault Hunter! Like me!
So, Nekrotafeyo's real? I thought it was just a myth.
So did I. Typhon DeLeon disappeared on his expedition to the Eridian homeworld decades ago. It seems he found it after all.
Tyreen said The Destroyer would be free soon. It'll rip the planet apart from the inside. If Typhon DeLeon knows how to save Pandora, we have to find him.
Never thought I'd say this, killer, but... set a course for Nekrotafeyo.
Drop pod's all set. You be careful down there!
WTF is that?
What the hell is that?
What is that?
What the devil is that?
No clue, and Tannis is fast asleep in her saurian. Try smashing those vines, Vault Hunter.
Looks like the local fauna didn't appreciate Maliwan setting up camp. Clear 'em out, killer. We have to find DeLeon.
Hey VH, looks like Maliwan tried to set up a Catch-A-Ride before they got ate. Ya might be able to reroute power from that force-field.
